MF = 3  NEUTRON CROSS SECTIONS                                    5247 1451
  BELOW 5.3 EV, THE CAPTURE AND ELASTIC SCATTERING CROSS SECTIONS 5247 1451
  WERE ASSUMED TO BE IN 1/V FORM AND CONSTANT, RESPECTIVELY.      5247 1451
  THE CAPTURE CROSS SECTION AT 0.0253 EV WAS TAKEN FROM REF./3/.  5247 1451
  UNRESOLVED RESONANCE PARAMETERS WERE GIVEN IN THE ENERGY RANGE  5247 1451
  FROM 5.3 EV TO 100 KEV.                                         5247 1451
                                                                  5247 1451
  ABOVE 100 KEV, THE SPHERICAL OPTICAL AND STATISTICAL MODEL      5247 1451
  CALCULATION WAS PERFORMED WITH CASTHY, BY TAKING ACCOUNT OF     5247 1451
  COMPETING REACTIONS, OF WHICH CROSS SECTIONS WERE CALCULATED    5247 1451
  WITH PEGASUS/4/ STANDING ON A PREEQUILIBRIUM AND MULTI-STEP     5247 1451
  EVAPORATION MODEL.  THE OMP'S FOR NEUTRON GIVEN IN TABLE 1 WERE 5247 1451
  DETERMINED TO REPRODUCE A SYSTEMATIC TREND OF THE TOTAL CROSS   5247 1451
  SECTION BY CHANGING R0 AND RSO OF IIJIMA-KAWAI POTENTIAL/5/.    5247 1451
  THE OMP'S FOR CHARGED PARTICLES ARE AS FOLLOWS:                 5247 1451
     PROTON   = PEREY/6/                                          5247 1451
     ALPHA    = HUIZENGA AND IGO/7/                               5247 1451
     DEUTERON = LOHR AND HAEBERLI/8/                              5247 1451
     HELIUM-3 AND TRITON = BECCHETTI AND GREENLEES/9/             5247 1451
  PARAMETERS FOR THE COMPOSITE LEVEL DENSITY FORMULA OF GILBERT   5247 1451
  AND CAMERON/10/ WERE EVALUATED BY IIJIMA ET AL./11/   MORE      5247 1451
  EXTENSIVE DETERMINATION AND MODIFICATION WERE MADE IN THE       5247 1451
  PRESENT WORK.  TABLE 2 SHOWS THE LEVEL DENSITY PARAMETERS USED  5247 1451
  IN THE PRESENT CALCULATION.  ENERGY DEPENDENCE OF SPIN CUT-OFF  5247 1451
  PARAMETER IN THE ENERGY RANGE BELOW E-JOINT IS DUE TO GRUPPELAAR5247 1451
  /12/.                                                           5247 1451
